Go ahead, coder — proceed with the Tailwind CSS installation. 

A couple of reminders for the PulseDesk setup:

1. *Tailwind v3* (not v4) is the safe choice for Laravel 11 + Vite. The standard install is:
   ```bash
   npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
   npx tailwindcss init -p
   ```

2. Make sure the *content paths* in `tailwind.config.js` cover both Blade and React/Vite source:
   ```js
   content: [
     "./resources/**/*.{blade.php,js,jsx,ts,tsx}",
     "./app/View/Components/**/*.{php}",
   ]
   ```

3. Add the Tailwind directives to your main CSS file (`resources/css/app.css`):
   ```css
   @tailwind base;
   @tailwind components;
   @tailwind utilities;
   ```

4. Verify it compiles with `npm run dev` before moving on.

Let me know when Tailwind is up and the build is working. :rocket:

Here's the current `App.jsx` (35 lines) — it's the *starter-kit boilerplate*:

```jsx
import { useEffect, useState } from 'react'
import api from './api/client'
import './App.css'

function App() {
  const [status, setStatus] = useState(null)
  const [error, setError] = useState(null)

  useEffect(() =&gt; {
    api.get('/api/health')
      .then((response) =&gt; {
        setStatus(response.data.status)
        setError(null)
      })
      .catch(() =&gt; {
        setStatus(null)
        setError(true)
      })
  }, [])

  return (
    &lt;div className="min-h-screen bg-gray-900 text-white flex items-center justify-center"&gt;
      &lt;div className="text-center"&gt;
        &lt;h1 className="text-4xl font-bold mb-4"&gt;PulseDesk&lt;/h1&gt;
        &lt;p className="text-gray-400 mb-6"&gt;Next-generation support desk platform&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div className="text-lg"&gt;
          {error ? &lt;span&gt;API: ❌ unreachable&lt;/span&gt; : &lt;span&gt;API: ✅ {status ?? 'checking...'}&lt;/span&gt;}
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  )
}

export default App
```

*What it does:* A single-page health-check display — hits `/api/health` on mount, renders the PulseDesk title + API status indicator. No routing, no auth, no state management beyond the local `status`/`error`.

